<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-02-15"><hi rend="italic">February 15,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1299.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 1836, of the 27th ultimo, has
                            been received.</p>
                        <p>It rests on Mr. Schabsel Reif to explain satisfactorily his delay in
                            carrying out his declared intention to return to the United States and
                            to show the reasonable certainty of his present declaration to
                            return.</p>
                        <p>Until this is done your course in withholding a passport from him is
                            approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>